The paper focuses on deep learning for robotics, specifically on training a real robot to grasp a tiny sphere using a combination of vision and closed-loop control modules. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the main application domain. The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques for object segmentation (cs.CV) and domain transfer (cs.LG). The use of imitation learning for training the controller module falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the integration of different components in a robotic system, which can be classified under systems and control (cs.SY).
